Type attribute for the script tag Possible values are:

  • MODULE - Use "module" as the script type

The page to which a new widget can be added Possible values are:
  • NO_PAGE - Don't add widget to a page
  • CURRENT - Add widget to the current page in the editor
  • PAGE - Add widget to a new page in the editor
  • LIGHTBOX - Add widget to a new lightbox in the editor

Which component types can be extended in containers Possible values are:
  • INVALID
  • BACK_OFFICE_MENU_ITEM
  • BACK_OFFICE_EXTENSION_WIDGET

View modes for how to open a component Possible values are:
  • PAGE - Opens a page in place of the current page
  • MODAL - Opens as a Modal over the current page

Category of pages this will be embedded on (single, many, none) Possible values are:
  • NONE_PAGES - It will not be embedded
  • ONCE - It will be embedded once
  • SPECIFIC_PAGES - It will be embedded multiple times on specific pages

  • NONE_PLACEMENT - It will not be rendered
  • HEAD - In the document head
  • BODY_START - Prepended before all children already rendered in the body tag
  • BODY_END - Appended after the last child already rendered in the body tag
